git basic knowledges

1.create git repo name, email info
git config --global user.name "chm"
git config --global user.email "chenhuming@gmail.com"

2.create a local git repo
git init

3.clone a local git repo from remote git repo
git clone https://github.com/beacoder/notes.git ./

4.add file into local repo
git add .
git commit -m "your commit message"
or
git add . & git commit -m "your commit message"

5.remove file from local repo
rm XXX file
git add -A . & git commit -m "remove some file"

6.show diff log
git status
git diff
git log

7.change the last commited message
git commit --amend -m "More changes - now correct"

8.revert to older revision
git log -> get the old version commit id
git checkout filename -> revert to files in the index or stage
git checkout commit_id -> revert to files commited

9.pull update from remote repo into local repo
git pull https://github.com/beacoder/notes.git

10.push local repo update into remote repo 
git push https://github.com/beacoder/notes.git